20who%20was%20then%207%2C%20was%20playing%20on%20the%20iPad.%20He%20had%20recently%20visited%20his%2010-year-old%20cousin%20and%20had%20since%20been%20playing%20some%20parent-approved%20online%20games%20with%20him.%20I%20love%20that%20they%20can%20connect%20over%20distance%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20I%20received%20a%20push%20notification%20on%20my%20phone%2C%20telling%20me%20my%20card%20had%20been%20used%20to%20make%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-data-form-of-currency-parents-decide-how-to-spend-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egaming%20transaction%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20iPad.%20I%20looked%20at%20Warner%20and%20asked%20if%20he%20had%20bought%20something%2C%20and%20he%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20you%20ask%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221160%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kristin%20Lewis%20and%20son%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682e3128c6ad288d148194eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22870%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKristin%20Lewis%20has%20an%20open%20dialogue%20about%20technology%20with%20her%20son.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kristin%20Lewis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20many%20things%20were%20going%20off%20in%20my%20head%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20want%20Warner%20to%20think%20he%20was%20in%20trouble.%20I%20asked%20him%20to%20show%20me%20the%20game%2C%20and%20he%20told%20me%20he%20was%20chatting%20with%20his%20cousin.%20When%20I%20looked%20at%20the%20screen%2C%20it%20was%20a%20random%20stranger%2C%20not%20his%20cousin's%20screen%20name.%20The%20stranger%20had%20sent%20him%20a%20link.%20Warner%20clicked%20it%20and%20made%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-gaming-pc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurchase%20for%20the%20game%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8e09bbc-55e3-4a66-8613-21f180684e87%5C%22%3EI%20immediately%20talked%20with%20Warner%20and%20locked%20down%20messaging%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20interaction%20was%20relatively%20innocuous.%20The%20stranger%20hadn't%20said%20anything%20inappropriate%2C%20and%20it%20didn't%20seem%20to%20be%20a%20scam.%20But%20I%20was%20struck%20by%20everything%20that%20could%20have%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sat%20down%20with%20Warner%20and%20explained%20that%20he%20wasn't%20talking%20to%20his%20cousin.%20When%20I%20said%20that%2C%20he%20looked%20scared%20and%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20who%20is%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20told%20him%20it%20could%20be%20anyone%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20while%20many%20people%20online%20are%20nice%2C%20others%20are%20not%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20to%20avoid%20talking%20to%20strangers.%20Then%2C%20I%20disabled%20in-app%20messaging%2C%20which%20I%20hadn't%20realized%20was%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8e6dc1b-c424-4557-b276-81041355075f%5C%22%3EI'd%20underestimated%20my%20son's%20tech%20capabilities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20morning%20made%20me%20realize%20that%20I%20need%20to%20talk%20to%20my%20sons%20about%20online%20safety%20before%20I%20think%20they%20need%20it.%20Kids%20are%20naturally%20curious%20and%20trusting%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20dangerous%20combination%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hadn't%20considered%20that%20as%20Warner%20quickly%20improved%20his%20reading%20skills%2C%20he'd%20be%20able%20to%20explore%20more%20on%20the%20iPad.%20He%20was%20a%20lot%20more%20tech%20savvy%20than%20I%20gave%20him%20credit%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20most%20parents%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20the%20time%20to%20research%20every%20app%20my%20kids%20want%20to%20use.%20That's%20why%20the%20work%20I%20do%20at%20Aura%20is%20so%20important%20to%20me.%20I%20want%20to%20take%20some%20of%20the%20burden%20of%20safety%20online%20off%20parents.%20I%20would%20love%20to%20have%20more%20of%20those%20decisions%20made%20for%20me%E2%80%94and%20my%20team%20is%20working%20toward%20that%20at%20Aura.%20But%20for%20now%2C%20there's%20still%20a%20lot%20of%20groundwork%20parents%20need%20to%20put%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb657496-9540-4eba-a7a6-11b2551b22a9%5C%22%3EI%20want%20to%20keep%20a%20positive%20outlook%20on%20technology%20with%20my%20sons%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20experience%20was%20jarring%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20the%20message%20to%20be%20that%20technology%20is%20bad.%20That's%20not%20the%20approach%20we%20use%20in%20our%20house.%20Instead%2C%20we%20have%20weekly%20tech%20check-ins%20where%20we%20get%20curious%20about%20what%20the%20kids%20are%20doing%20online.%20What%20games%20did%20they%20win%2C%20or%20which%20cousins%20did%20they%20catch%20up%20with%3F%20If%20they%20want%20a%20new%20app%2C%20we%20can%20look%20into%20it%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20our%20family%20lives%20far%20away%2C%20so%20technology%20has%20been%20a%20great%20bridge%20to%20build%20connections.%20Warner's%20cousin%20always%20Facetimes%20him%20when%20he%20walks%20the%20dog%2C%20and%20the%20two%20virtually%20walk%20together.%20That%20type%20of%20interaction%20online%20is%20always%20OK.%20Other%20interactions%2C%20like%20gaming%2C%20are%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20similar%20to%20snacking.%20The%20boys%20can't%20always%20have%20Doritos%2C%20but%20they%20can%20have%20a%20banana%20any%20time%20they%20like.%20They%20can't%20always%20play%20games%2C%20but%20they%20can%20answer%20FaceTime%20from%20family%20any%20time.%20I%20hope%20to%20empower%20them%20to%20make%20their%20own%20healthy%20decisions%20as%20they%20grow%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-son-outsmarted-me-online-we-both-learned-lesson-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751365321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682e2f2068a292900801f66d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-son-outsmarted-me-online-we-both-learned-lesson-2025-7%22%2C