0Meta%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-wins-ai-copyright-lawsuit-lawyers-fumbled-boies-schiller-flexner-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon%20a%20similar%20big%20legal%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGood%20news%20for%20all%20gen%20AI%20developers%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Adam%20Eisgrau%2C%20a%20senior%20director%20at%20the%20Chamber%20of%20Progress%2C%20a%20lobbying%20group%20funded%20by%20tech%20giants%20including%20Google%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20Nvidia.%20The%20Anthropic%20decision%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Blikely%20applicable%20in%20many%20cases%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d4cdbe7-1882-4c59-af1f-14e104de6d76%5C%22%3EThe%20plunging%20value%20of%20the%20written%20word%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20investment%20banker%20I%20spoke%20to%20recently%20summed%20up%20the%20impact%20of%20fair%20use%20in%20the%20age%20of%20generative%20AI%3A%20People%20will%20pay%20very%20little%20for%20the%20written%20word%20these%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20right.%20When%20copyrighted%20content%20can%20be%20scooped%20up%20for%20free%20and%20regurgitated%20in%20a%20slightly%20different%20form%20in%20milliseconds%2C%20the%20value%20of%20text%20online%20%E2%80%94%20even%20exclusive%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffrontier-content-survive-online-ai-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrontier%20content%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20plunges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Copyright%20Office%20is%20a%20lone%20voice%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20this%20discussion%20right%20now.%20It%20concluded%20recently%20that%20using%20copyrighted%20content%20for%20AI%20violates%20fair%20use%20because%20generative%20AI%20is%20flooding%20the%20web%20with%20mountains%20of%20additional%20words%2C%20images%2C%20and%20videos.%20That%20extra%20supply%20undermines%20the%20market%20for%20the%20original%20content.%20Judges%20seem%20to%20be%20ignoring%20this%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20former%20editors%20used%20to%20give%20me%20this%20advice%20when%20I%20wanted%20to%20write%20about%20issues%20like%20this%3A%20No%20one%20cares%20that%20much%20about%20the%20media.%20Some%20might%20say%20they%20do%20at%20dinner%20parties%2C%20but%20they%20really%20don't.%20These%20days%2C%20this%20industry%20is%20minuscule%20compared%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20economy.%20Go%20write%20about%20bigger%20things%2C%20this%20editor%20would%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%3A%20Meta%20holds%20about%20%2480%20billion%20in%20cash%20and%20marketable%20securities.%20That's%20almost%2010%20times%20the%20%3Cem%3Etotal%3C%2Fem%3E%20value%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Times.%20Meta%20will%20spend%20as%20much%20as%20%2472%20billion%20in%20capex%20this%20year%2C%20mostly%20for%20AI%20data%20center%20infrastructure.%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20is%20also%20offering%20%24100%20million%20compensation%20packages%20to%20try%20to%20hire%20single%20AI%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20Meta%20won't%20pay%20a%20dime%20for%20content%20for%20AI%20model%20training%20and%20won't%20pay%20when%20it%20uses%20this%20copyrighted%20content%20in%20generative%20AI%20outputs.%20Same%20for%20Google%20and%20most%20other%20AI%20giants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a918df63-053e-4ee3-8f3f-830d28adecc3%5C%22%3EWhy%20can't%20machines%20do%20the%20same%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-pure-internet-gone-low-background-steel-cloudflare-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20out%20in%202022%2C%20and%20I%20first%20realized%20that%20AI%20models%20were%20trained%20on%20mountains%20of%20copyrighted%20material%20without%20payment%20or%20permission%2C%20I%20happened%20to%20be%20visiting%20an%20old%20friend%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company.%20I%20brought%20the%20issue%20up%2C%20and%20this%20person%20replied%20with%20this%20argument%3A%20Humans%20learn%20by%20consuming%20copyrighted%20content%20on%20the%20web%2C%20in%20books%2C%20and%20from%20other%20sources.%20They%20internalize%20this%20information%2C%20process%20it%2C%20and%20often%20produce%20new%20ideas%20and%20content%20that%20is%20based%20on%20the%20original%20stuff%20they've%20read%20in%20the%20past.%20Why%20can't%20machines%20do%20the%20same%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20delivered%20with%20such%20speed%20and%20calmness.%20There%20was%20no%20pause%20to%20reflect%20or%20think.%20It%20was%20as%20if%20this%20Big%20Tech%20company%20had%20been%20preparing%20for%20this%20moment%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20the%20moment%20when%20everyone%20realizes%20their%20work%20is%20being%20used%20for%20AI%20models%20and%20chatbots%20that%20ultimately%20compete%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Google%20research%20paper%20that%20launched%20the%20generative%20AI%20boom%20has%20overtones%20of%20this%2C%20too.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F1706.03762%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAttention%20Is%20All%20You%20Need%3C%2Fa%3E%20introduced%20the%20%26quot%3BTransformer%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20world.%20This%20is%20a%20special%20type%20of%20AI%20model%20that%20ingests%20mountains%20of%20content%20and%20data%20to%20train%20powerful%20generative%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20did%20the%20Googlers%20who%20wrote%20this%20paper%20come%20up%20with%20the%20name%20%26quot%3BTransformer%26quot%3B%3F%20I%20don't%20know%2C%20but%20the%20word%20tackles%20the%20fair%20use%20question%20head-on.%20One%20of%20the%20tests%20for%20whether%20you%20are%20violating%20copyright%20law%20is%20whether%20you%20%26quot%3Btransformed%26quot%3B%20the%20original%20work%20enough%20to%20avoid%20infringing.%20Google%20came%20up%20with%20this%20Transformer%20name%20in%202017%2C%20a%20full%20five%20years%20before%20ChatGPT%20brought%20this%20new%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20copyright%20question%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20blogger%20Ben%20Thompson%20has%20a%20cool-headed%20and%20well-informed%20view%20of%20all%20this.%20He%20strongly%20supports%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20judge%20in%20the%20Anthropic%20case%2C%20agreeing%20that%20training%20AI%20with%20books%20for%20free%20qualifies%20as%20fair%20use%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Bcritically%20important.%26quot%3B%20AI%20learning%2C%20like%20human%20learning%2C%20is%20transformative%20and%20does%20not%20infringe%20on%20copyright%20when%20outputs%20don't%20replicate%20the%20original%20material.%20With%20copyright%20law%2C%20there's%20always%20a%20trade-off%20meant%20to%20incentivize%20creation%20without%20stifling%20innovation%2C%20he%20explained%2C%20and%20fair%20use%20exists%20to%20balance%20those%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ba3095c6-cc5c-4652-b0fe-ff0373e576f7%5C%22%3EA%20warning%20from%20the%20grave%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20will%20flow%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20basically%20any%20copyrighted%20content%20online%20is%20now%20fair%20game%20for%20AI%20companies%20to%20use%20for%20free%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20one%20prediction.%20This%20comes%20from%20the%20grave%2C%20but%20also%20from%20deep%20within%20OpenAI%2C%20the%20company%20behind%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuchir-balaji-marques-brownlee-openai-ai-training-data-death-llm-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESuchir%20Balaji%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20part%20of%20an%20OpenAI%20team%20that%20collected%20data%20from%20the%20internet%20for%20AI%20model%20training.%20He%20joined%20the%20startup%20with%20high%20hopes%20for%20how%20AI%20could%20help%20society%2C%20but%20became%20disillusioned.%20In%20November%2C%20Balaji%20was%20found%20dead%20in%20his%20San%20Francisco%20apartment.%20The%20city's%20chief%20medical%20examiner%20determined%20the%20death%20to%20be%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20he%20died%2C%20Balaji%20wrote%20an%20essay%20on%20his%20personal%20website%20criticizing%20AI%20companies%20for%20using%20public%20data%20without%20compensation%20and%20questioned%20their%20claims%20of%20%26quot%3Bfair%20use.%26quot%3B%20He%20argued%20that%20this%20trend%20threatens%20the%20sustainability%20of%20the%20internet%20by%20draining%20value%20from%20original%20content%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBalaji%20cited%20a%20study%20that%20found%20traffic%20to%20coding%20Q%26amp%3BA%20site%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-overflow-crisis-future-of-online-data-ai-world-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStack%20Overflow%3C%2Fa%3E%20traffic%20dropped%20by%20about%2012%25%20after%20ChatGPT's%20release.%20Developers%20who%20once%20visited%20the%20site%20to%20ask%20or%20answer%20questions%20are%20now%20turning%20to%20AI%2C%20reducing%20new%20sign-ups%20and%20community%20engagement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20undermining%20the%20web's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-killing-web-grand-bargain-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGrand%20Bargain%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Google%20and%20other%20tech%20giants%20used%20to%20crawl%20websites%20and%20collect%20the%20data%20without%20paying.%20But%20in%20return%2C%20they%20sent%20traffic%20and%20visitors%20to%20the%20creators%20of%20these%20sites%20so%20that%20they%20could%20make%20money%20via%20advertising%2C%20subscriptions%2C%20product%20sales%2C%20and%20other%20methods.%20Nowadays%2C%20Big%20Tech's%20AI%20bots%20crawl%20for%20free%20and%20send%20much%20less%20traffic%20to%20the%20creators%20of%20the%20original%20copyrighted%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECloudflare%2C%20which%20runs%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20networks%20on%20the%20web%2C%20rolled%20out%20a%20potential%20solution%20on%20Tuesday.%20The%20company%20launched%20a%20%26quot%3Bpay%20per%20crawl%26quot%3B%20service%20that%20helps%20content%20creators%20require%20payment%20from%20AI%20companies%20for%20accessing%20and%20using%20their%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECloudflare%20will%20block%20AI%20crawlers%20by%20default%20for%20new%20customers%2C%20making%20content%20access%20opt-in%20rather%20than%20opt-out.%20Major%20publishers%2C%20including%20Ziff%20Davis%2C%20The%20Atlantic%2C%20and%20Time%2C%20have%20signed%20on.%20The%20hope%20is%20that%20this%20will%20force%20big%20tech%20companies%20to%20pay%20to%20scrape%20new%20digital%20content%20for%20AI%20development.%20A%20startup%20called%20Tollbit%20is%20trying%20a%20similar%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20if%20these%20efforts%20will%20succeed.%20The%20core%20point%20is%20that%20humans%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20learn%20from%20copyrighted%20information%20for%20free%2C%20and%20machines%20probably%20should%20too.%20Reversing%20this%20might%20create%20even%20more%20problems.%20As%20a%20journalist%2C%20would%20I%20be%20able%20to%20read%20a%20Ben%20Thompson%20newsletter%20and%20incorporate%20one%20of%20his%20ideas%20into%20a%20future%20article%3F%20Maybe%20not.%20Would%20Thompson%20be%20banned%20from%20reading%20scoops%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20analyzing%20that%20new%20information%20for%20one%20of%20his%20amazing%20newsletters%3F%20Is%20that%20a%20good%20idea%3F%20Probably%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f1dbc80-d2a2-4066-ab8a-5d5b19a6f8d7%5C%22%3ESome%20predictions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20result%20of%20all%20this%20could%20be%20that%2C%20in%20the%20future%2C%20truly%20valuable%20information%20may%20no%20longer%20be%20put%20on%20the%20web.%20Here%20are%20three%20examples%20that%20suggest%20this%20might%20already%20be%20happening%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBen%20Thompson%20distributes%20his%20content%20via%20paid%20newsletters%2C%20rather%20than%20relying%20on%20free%20web%20distribution.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBloomberg%20runs%20probably%20the%20Western%20world's%20largest%20newsroom.%20Why%3F%20One%20reason%20is%20that%20its%20news%20arm%20is%20buried%20inside%20a%20massively%20profitable%20financial%20data%20business.%20Another%20is%20that%20Bloomberg's%20most%20valuable%20news%20content%20is%20published%20on%20the%20Terminal%2C%20a%20trading%20tool%20used%20by%20wealthy%20investors.%20This%20system%20has%20its%20own%20network%20%E2%80%94%20it%20doesn't%20rely%20much%20on%20the%20web.%20Bloomberg%20only%20publishes%20its%20best%20news%20content%20on%20the%20web%20after%20a%20long%20delay%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20its%20content%20just%20stays%20on%20the%20Terminal%20and%20never%20goes%20on%20the%20web%20at%20all.%20Surprise%3A%20It%20has%20a%20well-financed%20newsroom.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFinally%2C%20valuable%20content%20may%20be%20shared%20in%20the%20future%20only%20via%20personal%20meetings%20and%20relationships%2C%20or%20even%20through%20paper%20publications%20again.%20Anything%20where%20the%20data%20is%20out%20of%20the%20immediate%20reach%20of%20Big%20Tech%20AI%20crawling%20bots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20Microsoft%20started%20a%20new%20publication%20called%20Signal%20that%20explores%20the%20future%20of%20AI%2C%20society%2C%20and%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20published%20on%20paper%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-giants-win-copyright-fight-what-happens-now-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751364001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685dc545f748d8c055f4788e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-giants-win-copyright-fight-what-happens-now-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Big%20tech%20companies%20recently%20secured%20legal%20victories%20allowing%20free%20use%20of%20copyrighted%20content.%20This%20will%20reshape%20the%20internet%20in%20profound%20ways.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abarr%40businessinsider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-giants-win-copyright-fight-what-happens-now-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%