20gains.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAvoiding%20lazy%20equity%20by%20reinvesting%20can%20enhance%20cash%20flow%20and%20accelerate%20financial%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20variety%20of%20ways%20to%20put%20your%20money%20to%20work%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20you%20choose%20to%20invest%20depends%20on%20factors%20like%20your%20risk%20tolerance%20and%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuying%20real%20estate%20comes%20with%20its%20unique%20challenges%20and%20often%20requires%20a%20decent%20chunk%20of%20upfront%20cash%2C%20but%20has%20proven%20to%20be%20a%20wealth-builder%20for%20a%20handful%20of%20investors%20Business%20Insider%20has%20spoken%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20real%20estate%20investors%20like%20about%20owning%20property%20is%20that%20it%20opens%20the%20door%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-from-real-estate-cashflow-financial-independence-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20money%20in%20multiple%20ways%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20index%20has%20gone%20up%2C%20on%20average%2C%2011%25-12%25%20per%20year%20for%20the%20last%20100%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20Berkley%2C%20who%20spent%20much%20of%20his%20career%20on%20Wall%20Street%20before%20transitioning%20to%20real%20estate%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWith%20real%20estate%2C%20you%20can%20blow%20those%20returns%20away%20because%20there%20are%20four%20ways%20you%20can%20make%20money.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20one%20is%20easy%20to%20overlook%2C%20four%20investors%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224c83fd8d-458e-456b-8dd5-ff63e99d1829%5C%22%3ELeveraged%20appreciation%3A%20Using%20other%20people's%20money%20to%20increase%20returns%20and%20build%20equity%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20many%20ways%20to%20build%20wealth%20through%20real%20estate%20investing%2C%20leveraged%20appreciation%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Berkley%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-through-real-estate-investing-build-wealth-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20enough%20money%20from%20real%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20quit%20his%20finance%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReal%20estate%20can%20appreciate%20in%20value%20like%20other%20investments%2C%20but%20a%20major%20benefit%20of%20financing%20real%20estate%20deals%20is%20that%20you%20can%20borrow%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20(from%20a%20bank%20or%20mortgage%20lender)%20to%20buy%20the%20asset%2C%20but%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20share%20any%20of%20the%20appreciation%20with%20your%20lender.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22James%20Berkley%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63c986bd2a1e600018b8be00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReal%20estate%20investor%20James%20Berkley%20and%20his%20family.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20James%20Berkley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBerkley%20gives%20the%20example%20of%20two%20different%20home%20buyers%20who%20are%20planning%20on%20buying%20a%20%241%20million%20home%2C%20and%20both%20have%20%241%20million%20to%20spend.%20Person%20A%20wants%20to%20buy%20in%20all%20cash%2C%20while%20Person%20B%20wants%20to%20put%2010%25%20down%20and%20borrow%20the%20other%2090%25.%20That%20means%20Person%20A%20is%20paying%20%241%20million%20upfront%20and%20borrowing%20%240%2C%20while%20Person%20B%20is%20paying%20%24100%2C000%20upfront%20and%20borrowing%20%24900%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20house%20goes%20up%2010%25%20in%20value%2C%20it's%20now%20worth%20%241.1%20million%2C%20meaning%20Person%20A%20has%20made%20a%2010%25%20return%20(they%20put%20in%20%241%20million%20and%20now%20have%20%241.1%20million).%20Person%20B%20also%20made%20%24100%2C000%2C%20but%20since%20they%20only%20put%20%24100%2C000%20down%2C%20they%20made%20a%20100%25%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerson%20A%20can%20only%20afford%20to%20buy%20one%2C%20%241%20million%20home%2C%20but%20Person%20B%20can%20buy%2010%20%241%20million%20homes%20and%20control%20%2410%20million%20worth%20of%20property.%20If%20those%20homes%20all%20go%20up%2010%25%2C%20Person%20B%20makes%20%241%20million%2C%20while%20Person%20A%20has%20only%20made%20%24100%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20power%20of%20using%20other%20people's%20money%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20you%20really%20get%20rich%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Berkley.%20%26quot%3BThe%20bank%20doesn't%20require%20you%20to%20share%20the%20profit%20with%20them%2C%20so%20that's%20why%20I%20always%20try%20to%20lever%20up%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%20But%20you%20have%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20you%20have%20significant%20cash%20flow%20to%20cover%20your%20debt%20payments%2C%20otherwise%20you%20get%20in%20trouble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20debt%20is%20bad%2C%20he%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20bad%20if%20you%20use%20it%20on%20your%20credit%20card.%20But%20it's%20not%20bad%20in%20real%20estate%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you%20have%20cash%20flow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeremy%20Barker%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-invest-in-real-estate-creative-financing-commercial-leasing-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebought%20his%20first%20property%20for%20%243%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20just%20%2430%2C000%20of%20his%20own%20money%2C%20agrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20money%20the%20bank%20puts%20in%20is%20irrelevant.%20What%20matters%20is%20how%20much%20you%20personally%20have%20to%20put%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20providing%20his%20own%20example%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20buy%20a%20house%20for%20%24200%2C000%2C%20and%20you%20sell%20it%20for%20%24300%2C000.%20What%20do%20your%20friends%20tell%20you%3F%20'I%20made%20%24100%2C000.'%20Fair%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20let's%20say%20you%20only%20put%2010%25%20down%20on%20the%20property%2C%20so%20you're%20out%20of%20pocket%20%2420%2C000%2C%20he%20added.%20That%20means%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20took%20%2420%2C000%20and%20turned%20it%20into%20%24100%2C000.%20You%205%20times-ed%20your%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lower%20you%20can%20keep%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20you're%20personally%20putting%20in%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20higher%20the%20multiple%20goes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20puzzle%20to%20solve%20then%20becomes%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20much%20do%20you%20personally%20have%20to%20come%20to%20the%20table%20with%20to%20get%20the%20asset%20that%20gives%20you%20the%20return%20you're%20looking%20for%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e82b0ff8-54ef-4b03-b11a-75c3b16e006d%5C%22%3EAvoiding%20'lazy%20equity'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLazy%20money%26quot%3B%20is%20essentially%20money%20that%20isn't%20working%20for%20you%20%E2%80%94%20money%20that%20you%20have%20sitting%20around%20in%20a%20bank%20account%20earning%20next%20to%20nothing%20in%20interest%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20applies%20to%20real%20estate%2C%20as%20well.%20Financially%20independent%20investors%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-build-profitable-rental-business-retire-early-financial-freedom-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20a%20portfolio%20of%20rentals%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20give%20themselves%20the%20option%20of%20cutting%20back%20on%20their%20demanding%20physician%20jobs%2C%20refer%20to%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Blazy%20equity.%26quot%3B%20It's%20the%20portion%20of%20a%20property%20you%20own%20that%20isn't%20generating%20much%20of%20a%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20equity%20in%20a%20property%20tends%20to%20increase%20over%20time%20due%20to%20appreciation%20and%20paying%20down%20your%20mortgage%2C%20your%20return%20usually%20doesn't%20keep%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20give%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsemiretiredmd.com%2Fdo-you-have-lazy-equity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20example%20on%20their%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Assume%20you%20buy%20a%20%24100%2C000%20property%20with%2025%25%20down%2C%20and%20that%20property%20proceeds%20to%20cash%20flow%20%244%2C000%20a%20month.%20That%20means%20your%20return%20on%20equity%20(ROE)%20is%2016%25%20(%244%2C000%2F%2425%2C000).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESay%20you%20pay%20down%20the%20mortgage%20for%2010%20years%2C%20and%20your%20equity%20grows%20from%20%2425%2C000%20to%20%2450%2C000.%20Assuming%20your%20cash%20flow%20remains%20the%20same%2C%20your%20new%20ROE%20is%208%25%20(%244%2C000%2F%2450%2C000).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20let's%20say%20the%20property%20has%20also%20appreciated%20in%20value%20by%20%2450%2C000%20over%20that%20decade.%20That%20puts%20your%20ROE%20at%204%25%20(%244%2C000%2F%24100%2C000).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20your%20money%20isn't%20working%20as%20hard%20for%20you%20as%20it%20was%20when%20you%20first%20bought%20the%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20lazy%20equity%2C%20you%20have%20a%20few%20options%3A%20sell%20and%20upgrade%20to%20a%20more%20expensive%20property%20that'll%20cash%20flow%20better%20via%20a%201031%20exchange%2C%20which%20allows%20you%20to%20sidestep%20capital%20gains%20taxes%2C%20or%20do%20a%20cash-out%20refinance%2C%20which%20allows%20you%20to%20pocket%20money%20if%20your%20home%20has%20increased%20in%20value%20since%20you%20bought%20it.%20These%20strategies%20require%20time%20and%20money%2C%20so%20you'll%20want%20to%20consider%20how%20important%20or%20unimportant%20lazy%20equity%20is%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20can't%20stand%20the%20thought%20of%20being%20leveraged%20(being%20more%20in%20debt%20and%20having%20less%20equity)%20and%20want%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20loans%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%20However%2C%20the%20cost%20is%20lower%20return%20on%20equity%20and%20slower%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20couple%20explained.%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20goal%20is%20to%20achieve%20financial%20freedom%20as%20fast%20as%20possible%2C%20then%20you'll%20w